content.text:
No — **the pattern in `libs/react-components/src/lib/Avatar/AppAvatar.tsx` is not against React’s recommendation**.

What React recommends **against** is **defining a component inside another component**, e.g.:

```tsx
function Parent() {
  function Child() {
    return <div />;
  }

  return <Child />;
}
```

React’s docs say those nested component definitions are recreated on every render, so React treats them as a new component type each time, which can reset state and remount DOM:

- React docs: “Components defined inside other components are recreated on every render...”  
  https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/abe931a8cb3aee3e8b15ef7e187214789164162a/src/content/reference/eslint-plugin-react-hooks/lints/static-components.md#L13-L13
- And: “If you find yourself wanting to define components inside other components… that’s a sign you should be passing props instead.”  
  https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/abe931a8cb3aee3e8b15ef7e187214789164162a/src/content/reference/eslint-plugin-react-hooks/lints/static-components.md#L101-L101

Your `AppAvatar` is doing something different:

```tsx
const avatar = (
  <Avatar ...>
    {children}
  </Avatar>
);

if (!badge) return avatar;

return (
  <Box>
    {avatar}
    <Box>{badge}</Box>
  </Box>
);
```

That is just **assigning JSX to a variable** and conditionally returning/wrapping it. React docs explicitly present this as a normal pattern:

- “You can conditionally save some JSX to a variable and then include it inside other JSX by using the curly braces.”  
  https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/abe931a8cb3aee3e8b15ef7e187214789164162a/src/content/learn/conditional-rendering.md#L444-L449
- “Like before, this works not only for text, but for arbitrary JSX too”  
  https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/abe931a8cb3aee3e8b15ef7e187214789164162a/src/content/learn/conditional-rendering.md#L394-L410
- “React… you can use tools like variables and functions to tidy up complex expressions.”  
  https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/abe931a8cb3aee3e8b15ef7e187214789164162a/src/content/learn/conditional-rendering.md#L259-L259

### So for your file
`@libs/react-components/src/lib/Avatar/AppAvatar.tsx` is:

- **OK:** storing `<Avatar />` JSX in `const avatar`
- **OK:** returning it directly or wrapping it conditionally
- **Not the bad pattern:** defining a new React component function inside `AppAvatar`

### Rule of thumb
- `const avatar = <Avatar ... />` → **recommended / normal**
- `const InnerAvatar = () => <Avatar ... />` inside `AppAvatar` → **not recommended**

If you want, I can also suggest a slightly cleaner version of `AppAvatar.tsx`, but from a React-recommendation perspective, the current approach is fine.
